1. What is an Array:

An array is a container in Java that stores
    multiple values of the same type in a single variable.

2. Key Points

    Element must same data type
    Index start with 0 (first element)
    Access the element using index

3. How to create an array:

    int a[] = {10,20,30,40};     --- Declaration and initialisation

    int b[] = new int[1000];     --- Declaration
    b[0]=10;                     --- Assignment
    b[1]=11;

4. Access the element
    System.out.println(a[4]); -- Exception - Array Index Out of Bound
    System.out.println(b[5]); -- 0
    System.out.println(b[1001]); -- Exception - Array Index Out of Bound

5. Array Length
    System.out.println(a.length); // 4

6. Loop through Array

   Regular for loop

    for (int i = 0;  i < a.length; i++){
        System.out.println(a[i]);
    }

   Enhanced for loop (for each loop)

   for(int num : a) {
         System.out.println(num);
   }




